<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About - Roluthentify</title>
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/icons/icon.png" type="image/png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/custom.css">
</head>

<body>
    <header class="bg-amber-400 text-black w-full py-2 px-4 flex items-center justify-between">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
            <img src="/icons/icon.png" alt="logo" class="h-10 rounded-full">
            <a href="/" class="text-2xl text-white font-medium">Roluthentify</a>
        </div>
        <nav class="flex justify-center item-center gap-6 text-lg font-medium">
            <% if (loggedIn) {%>
                <a href="/guide" class="hover:text-white transition-colors duration-700 ease-in-out">Guide</a>
                <% } %>
                    <a href="/about" class="hover:text-white transition-colors duration-700 ease-in-out">About</a>
                    <a href="/contact" class="hover:text-white transition-colors duration-700 ease-in-out">Contact</a>
        </nav>
        <div class="flex justify-center items-center gap-1 relative">
            <% if (loggedIn) { %>
                <img src="/icons/user.svg" alt="user" class="userAccountToggler h-8 w-8 cursor-pointer">
                <div id="user-dropdown"
                    class="flex-col justify-center items-center absolute top-[120%] text-xs hidden bg-white ring-1 rounded-sm z-10">
                    <a href="/profile"
                        class="p-1 hover:bg-amber-600 hover:text-white transition-all duration-700 ease-in-out w-full rounded-t-sm">Profile</a>
                    <% if (role==="admin" ) {%>
                        <a href="/admin"
                            class="p-1 hover:bg-amber-600 hover:text-white transition-all duration-700 ease-in-out w-full">Admin</a>
                        <% } %>
                            <a href="/logout"
                                class="p-1 hover:bg-amber-600 hover:text-white transition-all duration-700 ease-in-out w-full rounded-b-sm">Logout</a>
                </div>
                <% } else { %>
                    <a href="/login" class="hover:underline underline-offset-2">Login</a>/
                    <a href="/register" class="hover:underline underline-offset-2">Register</a>
                    <% } %>
        </div>
    </header>
    <main class="min-h-[calc(100vh-6rem)] w-full relative">
        <div class="h-auto w-[75%] p-4 mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-xl font-medium my-4">Roluthentify</h1>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                Introducing Roluthentify, your all-in-one platform for building secure, scalable, and flexible
                role-based
                authentication
                and authorization systems using modern JavaScript technologies. Whether you’re diving into the backend
                with Node.js and
                Express, or crafting stunning front-end interfaces with React or Next.js, Roluthentify is here to
                simplify the process
                and guide you every step of the way. Built with developers in mind—from absolute beginners to seasoned
                full-stack
                engineers—Roluthentify takes the guesswork out of managing user roles, permissions, and secure route
                access.
            </p>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                At its core, Roluthentify empowers developers to implement robust user authentication flows, enabling
                features like
                sign-up, login, logout, JWT-based sessions, and secure API integration with ease. But it doesn’t stop
                there. What truly
                sets Roluthentify apart is its comprehensive focus on role-based access control (RBAC). You’ll learn
                exactly how to
                assign roles like admin, editor, user, and even custom roles to different users—and more importantly,
                how to protect
                specific routes and components based on those roles.
            </p>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                Imagine building a dashboard where only admins can view analytics, or an editor panel where only content
                creators can
                manage blog posts. Roluthentify breaks this down into real-world, production-level examples that you can
                instantly apply
                to your own projects. You’ll also find full-stack code samples and hands-on tutorials for implementing
                both client-side
                and server-side authorization checks using tools like JWT, cookies, middleware, and React context APIs.
            </p>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                Here’s what you can expect to find on the platform:
            <ol class="text-justify leading-loose">
                <li>
                    1. Step-by-step tutorials that walk you through implementing secure auth systems from scratch
                </li>
                <li>
                    2. Detailed breakdowns of middleware logic for Express to handle user access based on roles
                </li>
                <li>
                    3. Guides on protecting front-end routes in React and Next.js using HOC, conditional rendering, or
                    middleware in the App Router
                </li>
                <li>
                    4. How to store and manage user roles in databases like MongoDB and PostgreSQL
                </li>
                <li>
                    5. Practical examples of multi-role systems—like how to build SaaS platforms where different user
                    tiers
                    have varying levels of control
                </li>
                <li>
                    6. Best practices for hashing passwords using bcrypt, securing tokens, and preventing
                    vulnerabilities
                    like XSS or CSRF
                </li>
            </ol>
            </p>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                Whether you’re building a simple blog admin dashboard or a fully-featured multi-tenant SaaS product,
                you’ll find exactly
                what you need to secure your application architecture. Roluthentify is perfect for developers working on
                personal
                portfolio projects, startups launching MVPs, or teams looking to scale existing platforms securely.
            </p>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                And it’s not just about code—you’ll also find expert tips, checklists, and troubleshooting advice to
                help you avoid
                common pitfalls when dealing with user auth. From session expiration strategies to how to handle role
                changes
                dynamically, Roluthentify goes deep into the “why” behind the code, so you understand how it works, not
                just how to
                copy-paste it.
            </p>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                With support for popular stacks like MERN, Next.js + Node, and Express APIs, Roluthentify ensures your
                authentication
                system is not only secure but also modular and maintainable—ready for real-world scaling and deployment.
            </p>
            <p class="text-justify leading-loose">
                So whether you're tired of piecing together fragmented tutorials from random blog posts or you're just
                getting started
                with role-based logic, Roluthentify is your one-stop solution. It's time to level up your app security,
                boost your user
                management skills, and ship apps with rock-solid access control—all without losing your mind in the
                complexity of
                authentication systems.
            </p>
            <p class="font-medium text-lg p-4 text-center">
                Start building secure, flexible, and future-proof applications with confidence today—only with
                Roluthentify.
            </p>
        </div>
    </main>
    <footer class="bg-amber-400 w-full px-4 py-2 flex justify-between items-center">
        <p>Copyright &copy; | <span id="year"></span> | Roluthentify.com</p>
        <div class="flex justify-center items-center gap-4"><a href="/terms">Terms & Conditions</a> <a
                href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a></div>
    </footer>
</body>
<script src="/js/app.js"></script>

</html>